  "body": "Reduce fragility by decoupling as many classes as possible.\n\nBackground is best collected here:  https://wiki.hyperledger.org/display/BESU/Modular+Besu\n\nThe first phase is to include work tasks for research and prototyping, and will be timeboxed.  Example tasking would include things like:\n\n- research for analysis techniques, how best to measure coupling. How best to triage fixing coupled areas for maximum developer benefit.\n- evaluation of Inversion of Control frameworks to be used.\n- feedback loop to improve decoupling over time, vi CI processes.\n\n\nThe second phase will be for incremental implementation.  This is a general refactoring initiative, and is expected to be ongoing. Tasking here will target specific functions of Besu.",
